  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Hindi words 'Shubh' and 'Laabh'?",
  "response": "In Hindi, the word \"Shubh\" (\u0936\u0941\u092d) means \"auspicious\" or \"good.\" It is often used to denote something positive, fortunate, or conducive to success and well-being. \n\nThe word \"Laabh\" (\u0932\u093e\u092d) means \"profit\" or \"gain.\" It is used to refer to benefits, advantages, or material gains.\n\nTogether, \"Shubh Laabh\" (\u0936\u0941\u092d \u0932\u093e\u092d) is a common phrase that means \"auspicious profit\" or \"good gain,\" often used in the context of wishing for beneficial outcomes in business or endeavors.",
